children.subject: It was too hard and I don't have the math background since I have never taken any math courses here. I also don't think it's worth my time because I have no interest in data science or ML and can't see myself doing that in the future even though it seems like it's what everyone is trying to do right now.

history.content: From what I've heard, 162 is a must if you want to do software engineering. 164 would probably be a good idea too, it's recommended that you take at least one of 162/164 and have a good understanding of the other, so if you have the time and inclination for both, take them. I've heard that 160 is only really useful if you want to go into user interface/experience, but I don't really know all that much about it. Also, there's that new class on neural networks, cs 182, you might want to try that out if they offer it in the fall. Otherwise, it sound's like you've taken most of the software classes, so maybe try taking a 200+ course.

I'm deciding what to take next semester but 168 isn't offered so I don't have a lot of option left. I've taken all CS lower divs, Data 8, Data 100, CS 170, 188, 186, 161. I know I want to take 162 for sure but other than that I'm not sure what other CS class I should take. I was planning to take 189 this semester but decided to drop and don't want to ever take it. Is 160 a useful class and are there other classes from other departments you recommend if my interest is software engineering? Thank you!
